    "body": "Problem: Trying to execute code action on an active plugin without updates leads to nothing. It is more useful if code actions \"do something\" on a bigger portion of the confirm buffer.\r\n\r\nSolution: Suggest \"delete\" code action even for active plugins. Trying to execute it will first show a confirmation buffer with relevant warning of why this might be not a good idea. Confirming will delete a plugin.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nAddresses [this comment](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38194#discussion_r3196769573).\r\n\r\nDemo:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/30a4d10a-a19f-4eea-8b4e-ce1a239aea49",
